        "id": 3339
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-23T15:01:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please let me know if this approach works:\n1. Remove the global singleton openssl_sess_cache_t object, instead make it a per app object\n2. There may be two options to add this cache per each application: either add an opaque pointer in app_crypto_ctx_t, or we maintain all the cache objects (by app index) in openssl_main. I will figure out which one is cleaner\n3. If we want to enable/disable tls-resumption-cache per app, then probably we want to keep max-entries with the cache object (still, 0 means disable). Then, we\u0027ll need to add a new CLI like \"app crypto set app \u003cname\u003e session-cache-size \u003cN\u003e\" to re-size it at runtime, or, should we add a new tls-openssl cli to configure the max-entries for a named app. I saw each app may have multiple tls-profiles so it\u0027s more straightforward to make this max-entries app specific not profile specific.\n4. With that approach, we\u0027ll not do conditional setting for lines 1114 and 1115, as the client_ssl_ctx is a per worker thread object across all the apps",
